            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_jp.00032_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline rend="center">
                    <handShift rend="printed"/>
                    <name type="place">Office of JAMES CURPHEY,</name>
                    <name type="place">BANKER, BROKER AND DEALER IN GOVERNMENT SECURITIES,</name>
                    <name type="place">No.1 Pine Street.</name>, 
                    <name type="place" rend="right"><hi rend="italic">New York</hi></name>. 
                    <date when="1867-04-08" rend="right"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>April 8, <handShift rend="printed"/>186<handShift rend="manuscript"/>7</date>.
                </dateline>
                <salute>Sir</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Your note was duly received with order on M. Gray for a copy of your works. </p>
            
            <p>I have satisfied myself that no copy was delivered here&#8212;had such been the case it would have come under my notice&#8212;I therefore sent your order to M Gray and have received from him a copy for which you have my thanks </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours to</salute>
                <signed><gap reason="cut away"/></signed>
            </closer>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_jp.00031_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
